      <i class="ph ph-caret-right"></i>
      <span style="color:var(--graphite)">Tab-Ex 03 vs Aegex 10</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-z1">Zone 1</span>
        <span class="badge badge-atex">ATEX</span>
        <span class="badge badge-iec">IECEx</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--ash)">Comparison &middot; July 2026</p>
      <h1 class="serif text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] leading-[1.1] mb-4">
        ecom Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 vs<br/>
        <em class="italic" style="color:var(--graphite)">Aegex 10 IS</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed max-w-[600px]" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        Android vs Windows in ATEX Zone 1. The ecom Tab-Ex 03 is the market-leading Android option; the Aegex 10 IS is the only Windows Zone 1 tablet with full desktop app support. Same zone rating, fundamentally different platforms.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick verdict -->
    <div class="card mb-12">
      <h2 class="serif text-[22px] mb-4">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-[14px]">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#2563eb">Choose Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5" style="color:var(--graphite)">
            <li>&bull; Your field apps are Android or web-based</li>
            <li>&bull; Samsung Knox / DeX is part of your IT stack</li>
            <li>&bull; Weight matters &mdash; 690g vs 850g</li>
            <li>&bull; Budget is a factor (~&euro;3,200 vs ~&euro;4,500)</li>
            <li>&bull; You want the broadest accessory ecosystem</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#7c3aed">Choose Aegex 10 IS if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5" style="color:var(--graphite)">
            <li>&bull; You run SAP GUI, SCADA clients, or legacy .exe apps</li>
            <li>&bull; Your IT manages Windows devices via Group Policy / SCCM</li>
            <li>&bull; Users need full desktop-class computing in Zone 1</li>
            <li>&bull; Existing Windows peripherals (USB instruments, printers) must connect</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Spec table -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="serif text-[28px] mb-6">Spec-by-Spec Comparison</h2>
      <div class="card p-0 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-[14px]">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom:2px solid rgba(0,0,0,.08)">
              <th class="py-3 px-5 text-left font-medium" style="color:var(--graphite);width:35%">Specification</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-5 text-left font-semibold" style="color:#2563eb">Tab-Ex 03 DZ2</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-5 text-left font-semibold" style="color:#7c3aed">Aegex 10 IS</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Manufacturer</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Pepperl+Fuchs / ecom</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Aegex Technologies</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">ATEX Zone</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Zone 1 / 21</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Zone 1 / 21</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">IECEx</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Yes</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Yes</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Gas Group</td><td class="py-3 px-5">IIC</td><td class="py-3 px-5">IIC</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Temperature Class</td><td class="py-3 px-5">T4</td><td class="py-3 px-5">T4</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Display</td><td class="py-3 px-5">10.1&Prime; TFT</td><td class="py-3 px-5">10.1&Prime; IPS</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Operating System</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Android 13</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">Windows 10 / 11</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Enterprise MDM</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">Samsung Knox + Intune</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Group Policy / SCCM / Intune</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Weight</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">~690 g</td><td class="py-3 px-5">~850 g</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">IP Rating</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">IP68</td><td class="py-3 px-5">IP65</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Ambient Range</td><td class="py-3 px-5">&minus;20&deg;C to +50&deg;C</td><td class="py-3 px-5">&minus;20&deg;C to +50&deg;C</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Base Platform</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Samsung Galaxy Tab Active</td><td class="py-3 px-5">Purpose-built (Aegex)</td></tr>
            <tr class="vs-cell"><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Desktop App Support</td><td class="py-3 px-5">No (.exe not supported)</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">Full Windows desktop apps</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="py-3 px-5" style="color:var(--graphite)">Price (approx.)</td><td class="py-3 px-5 winner">~&euro;3,200</td><td class="py-3 px-5">~&euro;4,500</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs mt-3" style="color:var(--ash)">Green highlight = advantage in that category. Specs from manufacturer datasheets, July 2026.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Analysis sections -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="serif text-[24px] mb-3">The OS Decision: Android vs Windows</h2>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        This is fundamentally an operating system choice. The Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 runs <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Android 13</strong>, which means access to the Google Play Store, familiar mobile UX, and fast deployment via Samsung Knox. Most modern field applications &mdash; inspection tools, barcode scanners, push-to-talk, photo documentation &mdash; are Android-native.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The Aegex 10 IS runs <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Windows 10 or 11</strong>, which is the only option if your workflows require desktop-class software: SAP GUI, PI ProcessBook, SCADA HMI clients, or custom .NET applications that cannot be ported to mobile. For organisations with extensive Windows infrastructure managed via Group Policy and SCCM, the Aegex slots directly into the existing IT stack.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="serif text-[24px] mb-3">Ruggedness and IP Rating</h2>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 carries an <strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP68</strong> rating &mdash; dust-tight and protected against continuous immersion beyond 1 metre. This matters in washdown environments, offshore platforms, and chemical plants where tablets may be exposed to water jets or chemical splashes.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The Aegex 10 IS is rated <strong style="color:var(--ink)">IP65</strong> &mdash; dust-tight but only protected against water jets, not immersion. This is adequate for most indoor process areas but may be insufficient for offshore or outdoor refinery use. If your site requires washdown capability, the ecom has the edge.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="serif text-[24px] mb-3">Price and Total Cost of Ownership</h2>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        At approximately <strong style="color:var(--ink)">&euro;3,200 vs &euro;4,500</strong>, the Tab-Ex 03 is roughly 29% less expensive per unit. For a fleet of 50 tablets, that is a &euro;65,000 difference in upfront cost. The ecom also benefits from Samsung&rsquo;s broader accessory ecosystem &mdash; cases, docking stations, and replacement parts are more widely available and generally less expensive.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        However, if the Aegex eliminates the need for a separate Windows laptop at each work site (because field engineers can now run SAP or SCADA directly on the tablet), the higher per-unit cost may be offset by reduced total device count. Factor in software licensing: Windows Pro licenses add ongoing cost that Android avoids.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        For a full pricing breakdown across all ATEX tablets, see our <a href="/atex-tablet-pricing.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="hover:underline">ATEX tablet pricing comparison</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="serif text-[24px] mb-3">Where Each Tablet Wins &mdash; Honestly</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#2563eb">Tab-Ex 03 DZ2 Advantages</h3>
          <ul class="text-[14px] space-y-2" style="color:var(--graphite)">
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Lighter</strong> &mdash; 690g vs 850g for all-day carry</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Better IP rating</strong> &mdash; IP68 vs IP65</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Lower price</strong> &mdash; ~29% less per unit</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Samsung Knox</strong> &mdash; hardware-backed enterprise security</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Broader accessory ecosystem</strong></li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Faster OS updates</strong> via Samsung&rsquo;s AER programme</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2" style="color:#7c3aed">Aegex 10 IS Advantages</h3>
          <ul class="text-[14px] space-y-2" style="color:var(--graphite)">
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Full Windows OS</strong> &mdash; run any .exe, .msi, or .NET app</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">SAP &amp; SCADA native</strong> &mdash; no app porting required</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">USB peripheral support</strong> &mdash; connect instruments, printers</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Group Policy / SCCM</strong> &mdash; fits Windows-centric IT</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Desktop browser</strong> &mdash; full-featured web apps without mobile limitations</li>
            <li>&bull; <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Familiar UX</strong> for desktop-trained field staff</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Bottom line -->
    <div class="card mb-10">
      <h3 class="serif text-[22px] mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Tab-Ex 03 DZ2</strong> is the right choice for most new deployments &mdash; it is lighter, better sealed, less expensive, and runs the mobile apps that dominate modern field workflows. If your applications are web-based or available on Android, there is no compelling reason to pay the premium for Windows.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        The <strong style="color:var(--ink)">Aegex 10 IS</strong> is the right choice when Windows is non-negotiable &mdash; legacy SAP GUI, proprietary SCADA clients, or custom .NET applications that cannot be rewritten. It is also the better fit for sites where field workers already use Windows laptops and the tablet replaces (rather than supplements) those devices.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[15px]" style="color:var(--graphite)">
        For the full field: <a href="/best-atex-tablets-2026.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="hover:underline">Best ATEX Tablets 2026 &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="serif text-[28px] mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">Is the Tab-Ex 03 better than the Aegex 10 for Zone 1?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">Both carry identical ATEX Zone 1, IECEx, Gas Group IIC, and T4 certifications. Neither is &ldquo;more certified&rdquo; than the other. The choice is about operating system and form factor, not safety rating.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">Can I replace an Aegex 10 with a Tab-Ex 03?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">Only if your field applications are available on Android or as web apps. If you rely on Windows-only software (SAP GUI, SCADA HMI clients, .exe utilities), the Aegex cannot be replaced by an Android device without re-platforming those applications.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">Which has better long-term software support?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">The Tab-Ex 03 benefits from Samsung&rsquo;s Android Enterprise Recommended programme, which mandates security patches within 90 days. The Aegex 10 receives Windows updates via standard Microsoft channels. Both approaches have trade-offs: Samsung guarantees timely mobile patches; Microsoft provides longer OS support lifecycles (Windows 10 LTSC extends to 2032).</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">What about the ecom Tab-Ex Pro DZ2?</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--graphite)">The Tab-Ex Pro DZ2 (~&euro;3,800) adds an AMOLED display and S-Pen support over the standard Tab-Ex 03. If you&rsquo;re comparing against the Aegex primarily for the display quality or stylus input, the Tab-Ex Pro may close that gap while staying on Android. See our <a href="/ecom-tab-ex-03-vs-isafe-is930.html" style="color:var(--accent)" class="hover:underline">Tab-Ex 03 vs IS930.1 comparison</a> for more detail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-[13px]">
